<title>ITALY: Olivetti sees 1997 sales at 9 trln lire.</title>
<headline>Olivetti sees 1997 sales at 9 trln lire.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italy's Olivetti on Thursday estimated its 1997 sales at nine trillion lire, of which seven trillion will come from its information technology interests and two trillion from its telecom interests, including Infostrada, Telemedia and Omnitel.</p>
<p>This estimate was given by the group's chief executive Roberto Colaninno at an analysts' meeting today.</p>
<p>In 1996, the group saw sales of 8.304 trillion lire, and this included Olivetti's personal computer company that the group sold in January 1997.</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom +392 66129502</p>
